  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency shelter and NFI response to drought IDPs in Badghis</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The proposed intervention provides essential shelter and NFI support to drought displaced IDPs across four different settlement areas in Qala E Naw and Moqur districts of Badghis. Due to the severe lack of shelter options for IDPs in Badghis, In coordination and consultation with the ES/NFI cluster, IRC is proposing to distribute 2,000 emergency shelters to the most vulnerable drought displaced families living in the open or makeshift shelters in IDP settlements in Badghis. In addition, IRC will complement shelter provision with cash for NFI support to a minimum of 452 highly vulnerable households in greatest need of shelter and NFI support, as determined through household assessment data. Through household level assessment data analysis, IRC will apply harmonized shelter implementing partner selection criteria to conduct beneficiary targeting providing all necessary technical support for safe and effective construction of emergency shelter. Additionally, an updated rapid market assessment will be conducted in advance of a cash for NFI intervention for 452 highly vulnerable families who lack the capacity to meet their NFI needs after displacement. IRC will coordinate heavily with other ES/NFI implementing partners throughout the intervention, for a harmonized response, particularly in shared geographic areas. IRC will also coordinate with other cluster partners for holistic service provision whenever possible, and to increase the effectiveness of the planned activities for example, tandem NFI response with food response to increase the likelihood that cash will be used for meeting NFI needs. 
This action will allow for the scale-up of ongoing IRC emergency shelter and NFI response to drought displaced families, and complement other sector interventions to the target caseload. The proposed activities work towards filling a critical shelter and NFI gap currently facing drought IDPs.</narrative>
  </description>
